title.rendered: Alticor Inc Breaks Ground for UC San Diego Student Housing

content.rendered: The University of California, San Diego hosted a groundbreaking ceremony for the new East Campus Graduate and Professional Student Housing (GPSH) project. Representatives from Alticor Inc (contractor), Mithun (architect), the subcontracting community, and the local community attended. The $172.7-million GPSH-East Campus project is located in La Jolla, California, and is projected to finish in the summer of 2017.
